tessera (0.4.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Project renamed pam_certauth -> Tessera. The source and binary package
    is now `tessera`; the PAM module ships as /lib/security/pam_tessera.so
    and the control-plane binary as /usr/bin/tessera.
  * Paths moved: /etc/pam_certauth -> /etc/tessera, /run/pam_certauth ->
    /run/tessera, /var/lib/pam_certauth -> /var/lib/tessera,
    /var/cache/pam_certauth -> /var/cache/tessera.
  * systemd unit pam-certauth.service -> tessera.service; dedicated system
    user pamcertauth -> tessera; tmpfiles drop-in, polkit rule, SysV init
    and PAM stack snippets (tessera, tessera-optional, tessera-only)
    renamed to match.
  * Hook environment contract PAM_CERTAUTH_* -> TESSERA_*; log filter env
    PAM_CERTAUTH_LOG -> TESSERA_LOG; tracing/audit targets pam_certauth.*
    -> tessera.* (mac.audit unchanged).
  * Unchanged contracts: X.509 extension OIDs and their names
    (pam_cert_host_binding / pam_cert_user_binding / pam_cert_max_integrity),
    config.toml schema, and the IPC wire protocol.
  * admin-tools tarball is no longer shipped from this repository.

