pam-certauth (0.3.19-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * fly-dm greeter pivot #2: GreetString.desktop writer was no-op
    on production МКЦ-3 terminal (fly-modern hardcodes "Усиленный
    уровень защищенности" in the headline place). Replaced by a
    wallpaper writer that bakes host_id into the JPG that
    settings.ini [background].path points to. Opt-in via
    [fly_dm_greeter].update_wallpaper. Pure Rust (image + ab_glyph),
    no native deps added. See PR #36.
  * New CLI subcommand `pam-certauth dump-host-id` — probes EVERY
    canonical host_identity source (not only the subset in
    [host_identity].sources) and emits a TSV report. The
    `active_under_current_config=yes` column marks the source the
    daemon currently picks. `--output FILE` or `--usb` to write
    atomically. Used by operators after the clone-image bootstrap
    flip to discover what host_id_hash the hardware ended up with.
    See PR #38.
  * New /usr/share/pam-certauth/finish-bootstrap.sh — single-command
    transition from clone-image bootstrap state to production:
    atomic config rewrite (sources = ["override"] → real sources)
    with backup, pam-certauth check validation, daemon restart,
    automatic dump-host-id --usb. Flags --non-interactive
    (ansible), --no-restart, --no-dump, --sources. Idempotent.
    See PR #38.
  * New admin-tools release tarball
    pam-certauth-admin-tools-<ver>.tar.gz uploaded to GitHub Release
    alongside the .deb (NOT packaged into the .deb). Contains
    issue-service-cert.sh (per-host / wildcard / bootstrap modes),
    vault-pki-setup.sh, prepare-usb-flash.sh, README. Project-
    neutral naming throughout. See PR #37.
  * docs/install.md, docs/operations.md, docs/cert-issuance.md —
    cross-linked clone-image workflow.

