pam-certauth (0.3.16-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * fly-dm greeter pivot: revert the fly-dmrc `greeter-show-messages`
    cargo-cult from 0.3.15 and switch to the mechanism that actually
    works on Astra fly-qdm 2.15+ — /etc/X11/fly-dm/override/
    GreetString.desktop (freedesktop i18n .desktop file). The
    previous patch targeted a KDM/LightDM legacy key that fly-qdm
    does not parse; live testing on the Astra VM confirmed the new
    path renders host_id directly in the login-form headline.
  * New opt-in feature: when [fly_dm_greeter].update_greet_string =
    true, pam-certauth resolves the host identity on each daemon
    start and rewrites GreetString.desktop with the short hash and
    source, e.g.
        Устройство astra184 · host_id=abc12345 (dmi_board_serial)
    The original file is preserved as .orig on first run. Atomic
    write (tmpfile + rename). Silent skip on hosts without
    /etc/X11/fly-dm/. Failures log-and-continue (auth never blocked
    by a greeter write).
  * debconf prompt added to debian/postinst (en + ru) so dpkg
    install asks the operator whether to enable the banner;
    defaults to off. debconf added to Depends.
  * `pam-certauth check` validator pivoted to the new file: reports
    fly_dm_greeter_greet_string_customized / _default /
    _override_missing / _read_failed as Info records.
  * integrate-pam.sh: removed the --enable-greeter-messages /
    --no-greeter-messages flags and the fly-dmrc patcher introduced
    in 0.3.15. Script is back to PAM-stack-editing only.

