pam-certauth (0.3.13-1) unstable; urgency=high

  * Hotfix: ACTUALLY implement XDG_SESSION_ID capture in
    `pam_sm_open_session`. The 0.3.10/0.3.11/0.3.12 release notes
    declared the feature but the cdylib code path was never added —
    `pam_sm_open_session` never read `XDG_SESSION_ID` and never called
    `MonitordClient::send_update_session_target`, so monitord kept the
    auth-phase placeholder target on every login. Bankers' terminals
    continued to fail the USB-removal Logout/Lock action because
    `terminate_session` had no logind id to target.

  * Adds `crate::pam_helpers::pam_get_env_string` (thin `pam_getenv`
    wrapper) and a new `crate::xdg_capture` module containing a pure
    decision helper (`capture_xdg`) covered by unit tests for the
    three branches (XDG missing / present / IPC failure). The
    production cdylib calls `capture_xdg` after the MAC pipeline and
    before session_open hooks; an IPC failure logs WARN and never
    aborts session-open (best-effort semantics).

  * No daemon-side changes; relies on the `UpdateSessionTarget` wire
    contract already shipped in 0.3.10.

 -- Mikhail Korolev <mikhail@robonet.me>  Mon, 25 May 2026 22:00:00 +0300

pam-certauth (0.3.12-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Critical fix (Astra SE 1.8.3 production): USB-removal Logout/Lock
    action was silently dropped on banker terminals because our
    `session required pam_certauth.so` ran BEFORE `pam_systemd.so`.
    `XDG_SESSION_ID` was not yet in PAM env when `pam_sm_open_session`
    fired → `UpdateSessionTarget` never sent → monitord retained the
    auth-phase placeholder target (Tty/Display) → action handler could
    not call `terminate_session` and bailed with
    "Logout requested but session has no logind id".

  * Snippet split: `dist/pam.d/certauth`, `certauth-only`, and
    `certauth-optional` no longer carry the `session` line. The
    auth/account block stays inside the snippet so `@include certauth*`
    keeps working for the auth-stack integration that
    `integrate-pam.sh` plants near the top of the file. Existing
    manual integrations that referenced the snippet by path will lose
    the session-phase line — operators must re-run `integrate-pam.sh`
    after upgrade (the script now adds the session line explicitly).

  * `dist/scripts/integrate-pam.sh` two-include pattern: in addition
    to the auth-block `@include`, it now inserts
    `session    required   pam_certauth.so` AFTER
    `@include common-session` (anchor priority: common-session →
    last session-phase line → EOF). `--unintegrate` strips both
    lines. Idempotent on both passes; single backup per invocation.

  * Startup check `pam_stack_session_misorder`: scans each known PAM
    service file (`login`, `fly-dm`, `fly-dm-np`, `sshd`, `sudo`,
    `su`) and ERRORs when `session required pam_certauth.so` precedes
    pam_systemd.so / @include common-session. Fail-fast on daemon
    start, surfaced by `pam-certauth check` subcommand for
    pre-deployment validation. Adds INFO records
    `pam_stack_session_ok` and `pam_stack_session_no_systemd` for the
    common healthy and sysvinit/OpenRC layouts respectively.

  * Docs (`docs/install.md` §8 + §10): documents the two-include
    pattern, explains the snippet split, and rewrites the
    "Logout requested but session has no logind id" troubleshooting
    entry for the 0.3.12 placement model. The §10 entry now points
    operators at the new startup-check ID and the
    `integrate-pam.sh` re-run as the canonical fix.

 -- Mikhail Korolev <michael443959@gmail.com>  Mon, 25 May 2026 23:30:00 +0300

