pam-certauth (0.3.4-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Catch debian/changelog up with the workspace versions shipped in 0.3.2
    and 0.3.3 (PR #11, #12). Earlier releases shipped a .deb whose
    Version field said 0.3.1-1 even though the binaries were built from
    0.3.2/0.3.3 source — apt refused to upgrade because dpkg saw no
    version increase. This release fixes the metadata and tags 0.3.4.
  * 0.3.2 — USB partitioned-flash support: when the whole-device has no
    filesystem, pam_certauth enumerates partitions and accepts those
    whose ID_FS_TYPE is in the allowlist.
  * 0.3.3 — drop the LABEL=PAMCERT requirement; iterate all USB
    partitions with allowed FS until a .p12 is found. New config
    `max_usb_partitions` (default 8, anti-DoS). Fix:
    `pkcs12_path_pattern` is now honoured by discovery instead of being
    silently ignored; semantics changed to "relative path from mount",
    `${user}` placeholder supported, path-traversal rejected by the
    validator. Default remains `certs/user.p12`.
  * CI: new guardrail step that fails the build if Cargo workspace
    version and debian/changelog top entry disagree (prevents recurrence
    of the metadata mismatch above).

