pam-certauth (0.3.1-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Packaging: relax runtime dependencies so the package installs on
    Astra hosts and minimal Debian/Ubuntu deployments out of the box.
    - libgost-engine moved from Depends to Recommends with the Astra
      alternative: `libgost-engine | gost-engine | libgost-astra`. The
      GOST engine is loaded lazily and only when the verified cert
      chain contains GOST-signed certs, so pure RSA deployments no
      longer fail to install.
    - libudev1, libdbus-1-3, libsystemd0 dropped from the explicit
      Depends list — they are populated automatically by
      ${shlibs:Depends} from the binary's NEEDED entries.
    - polkitd | policykit-1 moved from Depends to Suggests; the PAM
      module and daemon do not invoke pkexec today.
    - Mandatory Depends are now limited to libpam0g, lsb-base and
      adduser (plus shlibs/misc substvars).

 -- Mikhail Korolev <mikhail@robonet.me>  Fri, 22 May 2026 22:07:06 +0300

pam-certauth (0.3.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * MAC integrity (МКЦ): new `[mac]` config section, `pam_cert_max_integrity`
    X.509 extension (OID 2.25.273824307386008814506455310913083078403),
    libpdp FFI binding under the `astra-mac` cargo feature. Orchestrator
    intersects cert max integrity with the user's МНКЦ and applies the
    resulting label to the session via fd-based labeling, closing the
    path-based TOCTOU window. Verified end-to-end on Astra Linux SE 1.8.4
    strict-mode kernel.
  * Strip: removed M-of-N approval, scope policies, and the `execute`
    subcommand path that shipped in 0.2.x. The remaining surface is base
    USB+X.509 PAM auth plus MAC integrity labelling.
  * FFI fixes: libpdp text grammar corrected to "level:ilevel:cat[:flags]",
    dropped `irelax` flag on `pdp_set_fd` (kernel rejects it through the
    fd-based API), link against `libparsec-mic` for `getmicnam`,
    `getmicnam` no longer free'd via `freemicent_r` — per man page the
    returned pointer is library-private static memory; the bogus free
    previously caused `free(): invalid pointer` SIGABRT in
    `pam_sm_open_session`.
  * Daemon: session registry moved from /var/lib/pam_certauth/sessions.json
    to /run/pam_certauth/sessions.json (tmpfs, volatile across reboot).
    Removes stale-state-after-reboot foot-gun and MAC-labelling churn.
    postinst removes the stale /var/lib file on upgrade; daemon.lock and
    caches stay in /var/lib.
  * postinst: raises ilevel=63 on /etc/pam_certauth/config.toml, ca/,
    crl/, host_acl.toml[.sig] when Astra strict mode is enabled (no-op
    on non-Astra / non-strict). Prints opt-in МКЦ activation notice.
  * МКЦ activation: shipped drop-in (mac-integrity.conf.example) now
    uses `PAMName=pam-certauth` with a paired session PAM stack
    (`pam-certauth.example` shipped to /usr/share/pam-certauth/pam.d/)
    that loads pam_parsec_cap.so + pam_parsec_mac.so. Replaces the
    earlier execaps-wrapper approach which failed under
    User=pamcertauth (no PARSEC_CAP_CAP → EPERM in execaps).

 -- Mikhail Korolev <mikhail@robonet.me>  Fri, 15 May 2026 20:43:40 +0300

pam-certauth (0.2.1-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Security: RFC 3161 TimeStampToken is now actually enforced when
    scope policy sets `require_timestamp_token = true` (was a silent
    no-op in 0.2.0). Both chain validation against the [tsa_trust]
    store and RFC 3161 §2.4.1 messageImprint binding to the signer's
    signature octets are checked (SHA-256/384/512).
  * Fix(cms): argv_pattern is now read from the signed
    encapContentInfo.eContent (breaking) rather than the
    tamper-vulnerable sidecar; re-issue work orders with
    `openssl cms -sign -nodetach`.
  * Fix(cms): signing-time is paired with each signer by
    SubjectKeyIdentifier / issuerAndSerialNumber rather than by
    positional index.
  * Fix(packaging): postinst enables pam-certauth-gc.timer and sets
    0750 root:root on /var/lib/pam_certauth/work_orders/.
  * Fix(misc): hooks docstring path corrected; scope-match dedup
    stable; fail-closed host_id_hash; monitord runs non-root cleanly.

