pam-certauth (0.2.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * feat(x509): new `pam_cert_scopes` v3 extension. Certificates now
    declare an explicit list of scopes (e.g. `bios.flash`,
    `cluster.drain`). The PAM module gains a `require_scope=...`
    parameter with `scope_match=any|all` to fail login unless the
    cert's scopes satisfy the configured set.
  * feat(execute): new `pam-certauth execute --scope=… --work-order=…
    -- <cmd>` subcommand performs per-action M-of-N authorisation
    against a CMS SignedData work order. Each signer must hold an
    approver cert (separate trust anchor `[approver_trust]`) with
    matching `pam_cert_scopes` and `pam_cert_host_binding`.
  * feat(policy): new `pam_certauth_policy` crate + TOML schema at
    `/etc/pam_certauth/policy.toml`. Scope rules declare `m_of_n`,
    `require_argv_pattern`, `pre_hooks`, `audit_level`. CLI helpers:
    `pam-certauth policy validate`, `pam-certauth policy explain`.
  * feat(retention): CMS work-order artefacts are retained under
    `/var/lib/pam_certauth/work_orders/` for forensic review.
    `pam-certauth gc --retention-days=N` plus systemd timer
    `pam-certauth-gc.timer` reap older entries.
  * feat(audit): every audit event carries `policy_sha256` so a
    sysadmin can detect post-deploy drift of `policy.toml`. Events
    flow via structured journald fields with strict sanitisation.
  * feat(hooks): hooks become a static enum keyed by name with one
    bundled builtin (`audit_critical`). No more arbitrary
    fork+execve from policy.
  * refactor(cli): `pam-certauth-monitord` is gone — the binary is
    now `/usr/bin/pam-certauth` with subcommands `daemon`,
    `execute`, `policy`, `gc`. systemd unit is `pam-certauth.service`
    `ExecStart=/usr/bin/pam-certauth daemon`.
  * refactor(ipc): IPC protocol bumped 1 → 2. `SessionOpen` carries
    `engineer_ski`, `engineer_cert_sha256`, `scopes`, `uid`. New
    message `GetActiveSessionByUid` lets `execute` look up an
    authenticated session by uid. v1 payloads still parse.
  * refactor(config): new sections `[approver_trust]`, `[tsa_trust]`,
    `[policy]`. Old configs still parse. See
    `docs/migration.md` for upgrade.

 -- Mikhail Korolev <mikhail@robonet.me>  Wed, 13 May 2026 00:00:00 +0000

pam-certauth (0.1.1-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * fix(pam): wire syslog backend for tracing subscriber. Auth-flow
    errors now land in /var/log/auth.log under syslog ident
    "pam_certauth" (LOG_AUTH facility). Production diagnosis no longer
    blind.
  * fix(pam): cert-binding X.509 extensions take precedence over
    [[user_mapping]]. pam_cert_user_binding / pam_cert_host_binding
    are the sole source of authorisation when present; the TOML
    mapping list is a legacy fallback for certs without the
    user_binding extension.
  * feat(deb): ship SysV init script (/etc/init.d/pam-certauth-monitord)
    via dh_installinit so non-systemd hosts are supported. Adds
    lsb-base dependency.
  * feat(deb): ship man(8) for pam-certauth-monitord.
  * feat(deb): three PAM-stack snippets (certauth / certauth-optional /
    certauth-only) and integrate-pam.sh --mode=2fa|optional|cert-only.
    Cert-only mode bypasses password chain entirely (lockout-strict).
  * docs: USBGuard / Astra ЗПС interop, USB-lockout pre-deploy
    checklist, on_usb_removed mode reference, three operational auth
    modes.
  * test: add leaf_no_user_binding fixture + un-ignore the legacy
    [[user_mapping]] regression test.
  * security: pam-certauth-monitord no longer runs as root. A dedicated
    `pamcertauth` system user is created in postinst; the systemd unit
    runs under this user with CAP_DAC_READ_SEARCH only. Privileged
    logind methods (LockSession, TerminateSession, PowerOff) are gated
    by an explicit polkit allowlist shipped at
    /usr/share/polkit-1/rules.d/49-pam-certauth.rules. Adds adduser and
    polkitd to package Depends. pam_certauth.so itself still runs in
    PAM-caller context (root for sudo/login) — that is an architectural
    constraint of Linux PAM and outside this change.

